result.name: Season Oyster and Wine Bar

reviews.text: A very disappointing dining experience. This place is priced like a slightly upscale place, but anything requiring preparation is treated as if you were at a truck stop diner. The sirloin steak I ordered was one of the toughest I've ever had, and the plate was drenched in clumpy balsamico and oil, making the steak, potato wedges and salad taste nearly the same. The salad I ordered for a starter (which turned out to be lettuce, cucumber, and half a cherry tomato) had the same dressing issue, and generally everything just tasted bland. It's an ok place if you want to chill out with some oysters and wine, but if you're looking for a made meal there are a lot better for the price within short walking distance.
nice food with acceptable price
Very nice food& wine with reasonable price!

A bit disappointing overall. You get a few choices of oysters (if available) and lot of other type of dishes including meat which is not what I expected (see menu if they allow the pictures).
Oysters are of ok quality and I'd really recommend to stick with the daily selected ones. They are small but compared to what I got after that is ok. Not so much taste though. I got them with a bottle of wine which was more than decent.
But my surprise (especially for a French man) was when I ordered 6 French oysters to taste the difference: have you ever seen an oyster the size of a hand?? You get for your money but not for your taste or stomach. This is not what I expected. I expected (of course more expensive) French oysters but a normal size and great taste.
Overall oysters is all I had so can't talk for the rest. Wine was good.
Disappointing for oysters since I was expecting quality rather than size.
Atmosphere is quiet.
By the way, who eats oysters with ketchup?? 😉
Had expensive but better tasting oysters at wooloomooloo.
Nice place for chilling with friends. Fair price for the oysters. Choices are not that much but quality is okay.

result.name: Season Oyster and Wine Bar 銅鑼灣

reviews.text:
餐廳裝修感覺有格調。彷酒莊的設計，燈光柔和偏暗，很適合三五知己邊食食傾。廚房部份作開放式設計，不時聽到食物烹煮的聲音和傳出香味，教我們食指大動。

精選生蠔 ($108) Fresh Oysters 12pcs (HKD108)
精選蠔不算大隻，味道偏向清甜，而且也算嫩滑爽口，一打的蠔作為頭盤，不錯。

意大利肉醬千層麵 ($128) Lasagna Bolognese (HKD128) 
芝士，麵和肉醬互相平衡，這款千層麵感覺面皮硬度適中，口感較煙韌彈牙，醬汁也足夠，有香味，整體不錯。

美國特級安格斯西冷 ($198) USA Angus Prime Grade Sirloin (HKD198)
這款西冷扒煎成全熟，當然不及平常愛吃的半熟鮮嫩，但感覺也不是太老，也有一些肉味，肉質纖維厚，頗具咬感。薯角也非常好味，煎得鬆脆。整道也是相當不錯。

自己本身鍾意食蠔，今日帶埋媽媽一齊去食餐好既！

聽朋友講Season Oyster and wine bar 幾抵食，所以一早book定位黎試

餐廳嘅裝修都幾特別，牆身釘滿左唔同牌子既酒既木牌，裝修帶少少工業風

跟住就睇下餐牌有咩食，選擇都幾多，而且價錢唔貴，咁就梗係要睇吓食蠔嘅餐牌先
原來凡係餐廳叫一支紅白酒，就可以以優惠價換購特價生蠔一次，$50/ 精選生蠔一打或者$50/ 中size生蠔半打

由於媽咪鍾意飲比較甜嘅酒，所以店員都介紹咗一支俾我哋， 味道唔錯都幾易入口

而我哋就選擇咗$50換購中size生蠔，雖然係中size，但係都幾大隻，係美國蠔，比較creamy同埋帶少少海水味，就算正價食都係$18/隻，非常抵食

另外仲叫咗個海鮮拼盤$298，有一隻龍蝦，兩隻元貝，一件大啡菇，兩件虎蝦同埋翡翠螺四件，舖面芝士焗到好香，焗到有少少脆身，所有海鮮都好新鮮

最後埋單每人都係$300，但食到咁多海鮮同埋生蠔， 仲有支酒添，真係10分超值

食正餐前決定同朋友去享受下生蠔既滋味!呢到要先嗌一枝白酒然後+$50可以有1打生蠔!
d蠔仲識得郁!仲跳跳紮 好鬼新鮮! 白酒經staff介紹來自智利 我個人覺得唔錯! 易入口得黎帶有少少fruity,
1大枝2個人分真係要少少時間去消化下 哈哈! 成打蠔食哂都未飲得哂! 不過anyway 我覺得酒係要慢慢飲既
如果用好少時間去消化,咁就唔係享受啦! 另外如果想分開嗌係無問題既 蠔有分LEVEL, 最平去到$9一隻咖咋!
而且地方好易搵! 近天后! 環境相當舒服! 岩哂一家大細或者情侶黎撐枱腳tim

A very disappointing dining experience. This place is priced like a slightly upscale place, but anything requiring preparation is treated as if you were at a truck stop diner. The sirloin steak I ordered was one of the toughest I've ever had, and the plate was drenched in clumpy balsamico and oil, making the steak, potato wedges and salad taste nearly the same. The salad I ordered for a starter (which turned out to be lettuce, cucumber, and half a cherry tomato) had the same dressing issue, and generally everything just tasted bland. It's an ok place if you want to chill out with some oysters and wine, but if you're looking for a made meal there are a lot better for the price within short walking distance.
nice food with acceptable price
